      "content": "My bad, I forgot I hadn't uploaded the snippet yet. Here it is:\n\n\"Section 4.2: Price Adjustments. The Supplier reserves the right to implement a variable surcharge of up to 5% on the base fuel rate during peak demand periods (defined as June-August and December) without prior written notice to SwiftRoute, provided such adjustments are reflected in the monthly invoice.\"\n\nDoes that clause give them the right to change rates unexpectedly? I really need a clear yes or no here so I can tell the board we're safe from price spikes.",
